[3] Georgia (Ajariya): ducks, preliminary suspected
Date: Fri, 3 Feb 2006
From: Natalia Pshenichnaya <crane@aaanet.ru>
Source: PolitBayki News Agency, 2 Feb 2006 [translated by Mod NR, edited]
<http://bayki.com/info/20325>

More than 10 dead wild ducks were discovered by fishermen in Batumi
port area. Batumi is the capital of Ajariya, in the southwestern part
of Georgia [map available at
<http://www.world-gazetteer.com/s/s_ge.htm>].
Some dead ducks were also discovered [on the beach near the port].
This information came from city administration.
Ajariya borders Turkey, where numerous cases of avian influenza have
recently been recorded.
According to the city administration, veterinary service staff have
already collected dead ducks, which are currently being tested for
avian influenza virus.
According to the Georgian Ministry of Health, no case of avian
influenza has yet been identified among birds or humans.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Results of the laboratory investigations will be appreciated; so
far, this event is regarded as a preliminary suspicion. - Mod.AS]
